data.title: list sports mates for for 'Laugh Now, Cry Later' visuals
data.meta_description: Drizzy also confirmed the title of his new album, Certified Lover Boy.
data.text:
Drizzy also confirmed the title of his new album, Certified Lover Boy.

Drake has dropped new visuals for his song 'Laugh Now, Cry Later'; if you could describe it in a word: money.

Collaborating with Lil Durk on the track, Drake takes things to the Nike World Headquarters in Oregon, where the camera follows him around playing sports, dropping serious cash on Nike apparel and as per usual, getting in his feelings.

Despite the music video looking like a shiny Nike ad, it isn't without a lash of self-deprecating humour as well.

Featuring cameos from sports stars including Kevin Durant, Odell Beckham Jr. and Marshawn Lynch, it's a fun one for fans who are awaiting Drake's new album, confirmed to be called Certified Lover Boy.
